---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../../config/site';

const title = 'MT opens regional hub in Dubai — MT Middle East';
const description = 'Press release · MT Valves and Fittings opens its first Middle East logistics and commercial hub in Jumeirah Lakes Towers, Dubai, with 48-hour dispatch across the UAE.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} lang="en-GB">
  <article class="max-w-editorial mx-auto px-6 lg:px-10 py-20">

    <a href="/articles" class="eyebrow text-steel hover:text-accent transition">&larr; All news</a>

    <div class="mt-6 eyebrow text-accent">Press release · April 2026</div>

    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display font-bold text-4xl lg:text-6xl tracking-tight leading-tight">
      MT opens regional hub in Dubai to serve the UAE and GCC markets
    </h1>

    <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-graphite max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
      A new logistics and commercial centre in Jumeirah Lakes Towers marks MT's direct entry into the United Arab Emirates and the wider Gulf market — cutting lead times to 48 hours and aligning documentation with local tender requirements.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-12 prose prose-lg max-w-3xl text-graphite leading-relaxed space-y-6">

      <p>
        <strong class="text-ink">Pallejà (Barcelona) / Dubai, April 2026.</strong> MT Valves and Fittings, S.L., a Spanish manufacturer of valves and fittings for fluid management, has opened its first Middle East logistics and commercial hub in Jumeirah Lakes Towers (JLT), Dubai. The new facility, operating under the brand <strong class="text-ink">MT Middle East</strong>, marks the company's direct entry into the Gulf Cooperation Council market after three decades of presence in more than 50 countries through its international distribution network.
      </p>

      <p>
        The Dubai hub holds permanent stock of MT's most demanded references for plumbing, HVAC, fire protection and industrial applications, with documentation aligned to the technical requirements of the region's main utilities — DEWA, FEWA, ADDC, SEWA, Kahramaa and SAWS. Dispatch across the UAE runs at 48 hours, removing the import waiting times typically associated with direct shipments from Europe.
      </p>

      <p>
        From Dubai, MT now serves the United Arab Emirates, Saudi Arabia, Oman, Qatar, Bahrain and Kuwait. The office operates Sunday to Thursday, with a bilingual English/Arabic team connected directly to engineering, R&amp;D and quality assurance at MT's headquarters in Pallejà (Barcelona). The direct line is intentional: technical queries, custom specifications and large project requirements are escalated and resolved without intermediaries.
      </p>

      <p>
        The decision to establish a direct presence in the GCC followed detailed market work conducted during the MT team's attendance at Big 5 Global 2025, held at the Dubai World Trade Centre in November 2025. Conversations and project data gathered during the fair confirmed sustained demand for European-certified products with local availability — demand insufficiently served by current channels.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-2xl text-ink mt-12">About MT Valves and Fittings</h2>

      <p>
        MT Valves and Fittings was founded in 1994 in Pallejà, Barcelona, by a team of engineers with extensive experience in the hydraulic sector. The company runs a vertically integrated operation covering engineering, R&amp;D, quality control and distribution, with a catalogue of more than 6,000 active references organised across two commercial divisions: Hidrosanitary and Industrial.
      </p>

      <p>
        MT holds <strong class="text-ink">14 active international certifications</strong>, including DVGW, WRAS, ACS, KIWA, KOMO, SINTEF, PZH, EAC, WaterMark, CSTB, AENOR, TÜV ISO 9001/14001 and CE/PED. The company operates subsidiaries in Mexico (MT América), India (MT Indic) and now the United Arab Emirates (MT Middle East), supported by an active distributor network in over 50 countries.
      </p>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-10 border-t border-mist">
      <div class="eyebrow text-steel">Press contact · MT Middle East</div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg">
        <strong class="text-ink">Email:</strong>&nbsp;
        <a href={'mailto:' + site.email} class="text-accent underline hover:text-accentDark">{site.email}</a>
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-lg">
        <strong class="text-ink">Phone:</strong>&nbsp; {site.phone}
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-lg">
        <strong class="text-ink">Hours:</strong>&nbsp; {site.hours}
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-lg">
        <strong class="text-ink">Address:</strong>&nbsp; {site.address.line1}, {site.address.line2}
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="mt-8 inline-block bg-ink text-paper px-6 py-3 text-sm uppercase tracking-wider2 hover:bg-accent transition">
        Contact MT Middle East &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>

  </article>
</BaseLayout>
